Title: Macroeconomic Forces, Systematic Risk, and Financial Variables: An Empirical Investigation
Journal: Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis
Pages: 559-564
Issue: 04
Volume: 26
Year: 1991
Month: December 
Abstract: This paper assesses the ability of financial statement variables to forecast sensitivities to systematic risk factors generated by a multifactor, macroeconomic forces model. Forecasts of beta derived from financial variables are shown to outperform naive, random walk forecasts, although Bayesian-adjusted betas perform as well as the financial variables model.
